 _ngcontent-ng-c1433446371=3D"" class=3D"research-step-description ng-star-=
inserted"><span _ngcontent-ng-c1433446371=3D"">(1) Research the current lan=
dscape of OS-level AI agents and their integration with financial services,=
 focusing on autonomous action frameworks like AI-to-Bank APIs and cross-ap=
plication automation.
(2) Analyze the security risks inherent in autonomous agents, specifically =
examining scenarios like indirect prompt injection, permission escalation, =
and "semantic hijacking" where an agent's intent is manipulated.
(3) Investigate the technical feasibility and limitations of the three prop=
osed ideas: blockchain-based activity ledgers for non-repudiation, contextu=
al permissions (time/location/amount), and multi-factor agent authenticatio=
n (human-in-the-loop vs. digital signatures).
(4) Explore emerging technologies that could add novelty to the solution, s=
uch as Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs) for secure agent execution, Ze=
