ase-out;"><p data-path-to-node=3D"0">To explain the <b data-path-to-node=3D=
"0" data-index-in-node=3D"15">Sentinel Intent-Binding Plane (SIBP)</b> to y=
our product and business teams, think of it as a <b data-path-to-node=3D"0"=
 data-index-in-node=3D"105">"Digital Notary"</b> that sits between an auton=
omous AI agent and the bank's vault.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"1">The Pro=
blem: Why Traditional Security Isn't Enough</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"2">=
Traditional banking security is built for humans and static programs. AI ag=
ents represent a new type of risk because:</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"3"><=
li><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0" data-index=
-in-node=3D"0">The "Language Trap":</b> AI models cannot distinguish betwee=
n a legitimate instruction from a boss and a hidden "trap" in a document or=
 email. They process both as commands to follow.</p></li><li><p data-path-t=
o-node=3D"3,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Th=
e "Force Multiplier" Risk:</b> An agent usually has the same permissions as=
 the human user. If the human can delete a file or move $10,000, the agent =
can do it 10,000 times in a second if it is tricked.</p></li><li><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"3,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0=
">Missing "Meaning" Checks:</b> Current firewalls check if a password is co=
rrect. They do <b data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"84">not=
</b> check if the <i data-path-to-node=3D"3,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"101"=
>intent</i> of the request (e.g., "Pay this random person") matches the ori=
ginal goal (e.g., "Reconcile my monthly utility bills").</p></li><li><p dat=
a-path-to-node=3D"3,3,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,3,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"0">The "Whitespace" Problem:</b> 80% of banking work happens between sy=
stems (e.g., matching an invoice in email to a payment in the ledger). This=
 "messy middle" is where agents are most likely to make mistakes or be mani=
pulated.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"4">The Solution: Sentinel In=
tent-Binding Plane (SIBP)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"5">The SIBP solves th=
is by adding three "speed bumps" to every agent action:</p><ul data-path-to=
-node=3D"6"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"6,0,0" id=3D"p-rc_58b3714bf90fc985-=
