"ltr" style=3D"--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: ease=
-out;"><p data-path-to-node=3D"0">The <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index=
-in-node=3D"4">Sentinel Intent-Binding Plane (SIBP)</b> is an architectural=
 "Control Plane" that does not live in just one place. Instead, it is a <b =
data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index-in-node=3D"132">distributed system</b> w=
ith components that reside both on the user=E2=80=99s device (at the OS lev=
el) and within the bank=E2=80=99s secure cloud infrastructure.</p><h3 data-=
path-to-node=3D"1">Where the SIBP System is Located</h3><p data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"2">The system functions as a protective bridge between the "creative i=
ntelligence" of the AI agent and the "deterministic safety" of the bank's l=
edger.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"3"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0"><b=
 data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">On the User=E2=80=99s=
 Device (OS Level):</b> A lightweight "Sentinel Agent" or "Security Plane" =
can sit directly on the device as a sidecar or proxy. Its job is to watch t=
he agent=E2=80=99s reasoning in real-time, catch "Goal Hijacking" attempts =
before they leave the computer, and manage the <b data-path-to-node=3D"3,0,=
0" data-index-in-node=3D"273">Hardware Root of Trust</b> (like a physical s=
ecurity key or biometric sensor).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0=
"><b data-path-to-node=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">In the Bank=E2=80=
=99s Infrastructure:</b> The primary "Authority Layer" and "Policy Engine" =
live on the bank=E2=80=99s servers. This ensures that even if an attacker c=
ompletely takes over the user=E2=80=99s computer, they cannot bypass the se=
curity rules because the bank=E2=80=99s gateway must still issue a <b data-=
path-to-node=3D"3,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"273">Semantic Decision Token</=
b> before any money moves.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"4">How Age=
nts Know to Interact with SIBP</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"5">AI agents int=
eract with the SIBP through a "Standardized Handshake" using the <b data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"5" data-index-in-node=3D"78">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</b>=
. Here is how the agent "sees" and uses the system:</p><ul data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"6"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"6,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"6,0,0" d=
ata-index-in-node=3D"0">The Single Entry Point:</b> Instead of giving an ag=
ent access to dozens of different banking databases and tools, the bank poi=
nts the agent to <b data-path-to-node=3D"6,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"139">=
one single endpoint</b>: the SIBP Gateway. To the agent, the SIBP <i data-p=
ath-to-node=3D"6,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"201">is</i> the bank.</p></li><=
li><p data-path-to-node=3D"6,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"6,1,0" data-index=
-in-node=3D"0">Filtered Discovery:</b> When the agent starts a task, it use=
s the MCP to ask, "What tools can I use?". The SIBP evaluates the agent=E2=
=80=99s current context (Who is it? Where is it? What time is it?) and only=
 "advertises" the tools that are safe for that specific moment. If an agent=
 isn't allowed to make a $10,000 transfer at 3 AM from a new country, the "=
Transfer Tool" simply disappears from its view.</p></li><li><p data-path-to=
-node=3D"6,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"6,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The=
 Intent Requirement:</b> Before the system allows the agent to call a tool =
(like <code data-path-to-node=3D"6,2,0" data-index-in-node=3D"80">pay_invoi=
ce</code>), the agent must "declare its intent" in a structured format. The=
 agent knows it cannot proceed without receiving a digital "ActionApproved"=
 signal from the SIBP, which it then presents to the bank's API as its "tic=
ket" to perform the transaction.</p></li></ul><p data-path-to-node=3D"7"><b=
 data-path-to-node=3D"7" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Summary for the team:</b>
The SIBP is like a <b data-path-to-node=3D"7" data-index-in-node=3D"41">"Se=
curity Border Crossing"</b>. The agent is the traveler, and the MCP is the =
passport it carries. The agent knows it must go through the SIBP because it=
 is the only path to reach its destination (the bank's money). The SIBP che=
cks the "passport" and the "reason for travel" at the border (the gateway) =
before letting the agent through.</p></div></message-content><!----></div><=
