u give a voice or text command to your OS agent: <i data-path-to-node=3D"4"=
 data-index-in-node=3D"72">"Find the best high-yield savings account and mo=
ve $2,000 from my checking to it."</i> This is called the <b data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"4" data-index-in-node=3D"174">Natural Language Request (NLR)</b>.</p=
><h4 data-path-to-node=3D"5">2. Creating the "Digital Contract" (Intent Par=
ser)</h4><p data-path-to-node=3D"6">Before the agent is allowed to browse t=
he web, the <b data-path-to-node=3D"6" data-index-in-node=3D"51">Intent Par=
ser</b> translates your vague words into a strict, machine-readable "Contra=
ct" known as an <b data-path-to-node=3D"6" data-index-in-node=3D"148">Inten=
t Mandate</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"7"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"7=
,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"7,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">What it does:=
</b> It extracts the "Who," "What," and "How much."</p></li><li><p data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"7,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"7,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0"=
>The Anchor:</b> The SIBP creates a cryptographic fingerprint (a SHA-256 ha=
sh) of your original words and attaches it to this mandate. This "anchors" =
the task so it cannot be changed later without the system noticing.</p></li=
></ul><h4 data-path-to-node=3D"8">3. The "Hidden Trap" Interaction</h4><p d=
