>Autonomous Mode</b>. In this mode, the human is not present at the moment =
of the transaction, but they have already provided a "Standing Intent" thro=
ugh a <b data-path-to-node=3D"1" data-index-in-node=3D"229">Policy-Based Au=
thorization</b>.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"2">How Autonomous Intent Works=
</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"3">Instead of a new prompt for every payment, =
the system uses a <b data-path-to-node=3D"3" data-index-in-node=3D"61">Dele=
gation Chain</b>. The human sets high-level "Intent Mandates" (pre-approval=
s) that act as the agent=E2=80=99s "employment contract".</p><ul data-path-=
to-node=3D"4"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"4,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"4,=
0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Human Role:</b> Sets the boundaries and high-=
level goals (e.g., "Maintain a $5,000 liquidity buffer" or "Pay all valid i=
nvoices under $1,000 automatically").</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"4=
,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"4,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Agent Role:</=
b> Continuously observes the environment. If it detects a condition that re=
quires action (e.g., an account balance is low or an invoice arrives), it <=
b data-path-to-node=3D"4,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"158">self-generates</b>=
 a specific intent to act.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"5">Example=
: The "Smart Maintenance" Agent (Autonomous)</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"6"=
><b data-path-to-node=3D"6" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Problem:</b> A bus=
iness fleet manager has an agent that monitors delivery trucks. One truck t=
riggers a sensor showing its brakes are worn out.</p><ol start=3D"1" data-p=
